name: Colored Engraving on Locket. Choose Blue, Purple, Green, Pink, or Red
description:
Colored engraving on a locket. You can choose blue, purple, green, pink, or red colored handwriting on it. The locket is brass and copper and comes on a sterling silver chain. You can choose a 16, 18, or 20 inch chain. I color the locket also (this is called patina).

Red

You may choose your own words to be engraved. I suggest the names of loved ones and/or special dates like anniversary and birthdates. Inspirational quotations or phrases from your wedding vows are also a good choice. This locket is about 1.5 inches in diameter.

I've engraved this locket with an original poem that I wrote. The locket itself is made of vintage brass and copper. I've applied different patinas, and then colored selected parts with pencil. I've lacquered the locket to seal in the color.

Since this is a locket for wearing (gently). I will not engrave or color the back of the locket. If you intend to put pictures on the inside, let me know and I will not engrave or color the inside. I do put a lacquer on the locket in order to protect the patina / coloring. As long as you handle the locket gently, the lacquer will not wear off (except for the very back). As for the lacquer on the back wearing off, you may either relacquer it at home with clear nail polish, or send it back to me for touchups for a minimal charge. You can also let the lacquer wear off in the back, which allows the brass to patina and gives it some character. I suggest this as the best way.

This locket is one of a kind. This particular locket has become part of one of my larger projects called Souls and Rain Curtain. Your locket will look different because of the randomness of the patina. But it will have the blue words on it and have the same degree/extent of patination.

I'm limited as to the number of photos I can upload for each item on Etsy, so I'm putting up more photos of the lockets on my website http://www.crazypenguin.com/jewelry . Or, you can email me for additional photos.

I surfed on the wave,

water which is eternal and unchanging,

14k white palladium gold is gold with *no* nickel in the alloy. instead of nickel as the whitening agent, they use palladium. Palladium is a member of the platinum family. Palladium gold is whiter than nickel white gold. It achieves the high white metal look found in jewelry stores without plating. (Most jewelry stores plate their white gold with rhodium to get the high white color).

I can also saw heart shapes outside of the back of the setting. When you take the ring off and hold it up to the light, there will be two light white hearts glowing inside the moonstone. When you put the ring back on, no light shines through the back, so the hearts disappear. Discreet, and just for you and your fiance.

My hammered 1mm and 2mm wedding bands will fit flush against this ring, making a perfect wedding set. 

Moonstone was a popular stone used in Art Nouveau jewelry of the 1920's. It has a shimmering characteristic called "adularescence."

Moonstone engagement ring is custom-made, made-to-order and takes 2-3 weeks. US quarter sizes 5-12. You may email me your ring size.

What Percentage % of Gold is in 18k?
18k gold is 75% gold. The rest (25%) is half silver and half copper.

How do you calculate the percentage of gold in 22k?
24k gold is 100% gold. So, 24 divided by 24 = 1 or 100%
22 divided by 24 = .9167. Multiply that by 100 to get 91.67%
